---
description: Enforce backend layering and repository-only data access
alwaysApply: true
---

# Backend Layering (Feature-Driven)

- For backend features, use this flow: `routes -> handler/controller -> service -> repository -> models/db`.
- Keep handlers/controllers transport-only:
  - parse request input
  - call service
  - map service errors to HTTP responses
- Keep services business-only:
  - orchestrate use-case logic
  - call repositories
  - no direct ORM/model/database access
- Keep repositories data-only:
  - all `Model.find*`, `create`, `update`, `destroy`, `bulkCreate`, `increment/decrement`
  - all transaction boundaries (`sequelize.transaction`)

# Non-negotiable Rule

- Never execute direct database operations outside repositories.
- Forbidden outside repositories:
  - `sequelize.transaction(...)`
  - `Model.find*`, `Model.create`, `Model.update`, `Model.destroy`
  - `instance.update`, `instance.destroy`, `Model.bulkCreate`, `Model.increment/decrement`

# Structure

- Place feature code under `api/src/modules/<feature>/`.
- Keep one concern per file:
  - `<feature>.routes.ts`
  - `<feature>.handler.ts` (or `<feature>.controller.ts`)
  - `<feature>.service.ts`
  - `<feature>.repository.ts`
